  "description": "Agnar August Hall was a Swedish hospital physician and expert in ear, nose, and throat diseases. He was born on April 10th, 1899 in Alvesta, Kronoberg County, and earned a Bachelor's degree in medicine from Karolinska Institute in 1924 and a medical degree there in 1928. He studied abroad in several countries, including the United States, and served in various assistant and temporary doctor positions before becoming a physician at Norrköping Hospital in 1939. He was also the chairman of the Norrköping chapter of the Swedish Red Cross and of the local branch of the Swedish Association for the Deaf. Throughout his career, he wrote several papers in professional journals." 
